titleInfo.title: Bischoff, et al v. Brittain, et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Judge Kimberly J. Mueller on 10/10/2014 GRANTING 4 Plaintiffs Motion for preliminary injunction; Defendants Sandra Brittain, Keith Johnson and RZM Investments Enterprise, LLC shall allow plaintiffs to remain in and use and enjoy their apartments at the Birchwood Gardens apartment complex, and shall not terminate plaintiffs Scott Bischoff's and Leron Dempsey's tenancies based on discriminatory reasons in violation of the FHA so long as plaintiffs continue to pay their monthly rent; Plaintiffs Scott Bischoff and Leron Dempsey shall continue to pay rent to defendants at the current monthly rate as the rent becomes due. Payment of rent shall be delivered to the on-site manager's office; this preliminary injunction will remain in effect until a final determination of plaintiffs' claims; no bond is required at this time. (Reader, L)

titleInfo.title: Bischoff, et al v. Brittain, et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Carolyn K. Delaney on 10/15/2015 ORDERING that the parties are directed to meet and confer regarding a stipulated protective order. No later than 10/28/2015, the parties shall submit a stipulated protective order. If the parties cannot agree on the terms of the protective order, no later than 10/28/2015, plaintiffs shall submit a proposed protective order and defendants shall file any objections thereto. The 44 motion to compel is GRANTED. All responsive documents shall be produced, without objection, no later than 11/6/2015. Discovery produced pursuant to this order shall be subject to the protective order. (Zignago, K.)
